Why do you need the "run at startup" permission? I can only paddle 6 months of the year, that's 180 days where I have no use of updated tide times, but still have to wait on your updates.
replyContent: Doing it this way ensures that the app always has the latest tidal information for when you need it. It only updates once per day, in the middle of the night when your phone is usually on charge. It does this by making just a single web request and only updates the tides for the locations you have checked. It should have close to no impact on you.

This app is simple yet very comprehensive, it is reliable and cost-effective so what more could you ask for. Excellent piece of work.
Fast and locates your area through built in gps which most phones have now.
Easy to use and covers absolutely every where there's a tide!
Useful and practical.
My Tides Pro
Until this app I didn't realise how much I could use 'user friendly' tide tables
Simple. Basic. Does what it says it'll do.
Accurate  forecasts for  regions.
Staying on the Gulf of Maine with my family and always knew exactly what the tides were up to.
Not bad.

I can see it's usefulness and can see that it could be brilliant for us!!!  However,  we fish SEVERAL places along the Ocheegee and Savannah Rivers.  The App is missing about 95% of just the public boat landings. I would REALLY like to see an ADD LOCATION feature to go with the See your most recent visited feature.  High tide can vary a lot depending where on the river you are.
Good app, easy interface
Does exactly what I need
A very good tide table ap.
Seems to be accurate and also is fast loading. Newfoundland
Easy to use....good overall app.

I got this app because it said information is downloaded for when there is no internet connection - but standing on top of a cliff i have no network either so i assume it cant work out where i am. So, no information is shown. So i am unhappy and don't like this app. it needs to default to my last set of info in the circumstances i indicated and show those with warnings about the beach it is showing and dates issues. for myself i use the same beach 99% of the time so it should understand that as well even to the point that once a week on wifi it should refresh its information.
Great
Very handy app to have on my phone.
If you want high and low water times and heights at predetermined points then it does the job.  If you want anything more you are likely to be disappointed.
Good
A very good app, for my requirements, as river watcher and bank walker.
What a shame you cannot save a favourite location, otherwise this would be a 5!  Please advise if you upgrade this app so existing users can upgrade.
Great app
Great app.  Does what it is supposed to do elegantly and smoothly. Caters for South Africa unlike some competitors.
Fast and efficient.  Hasn't let me down.
It needs ability to store favourite locations, a week in advance table and a widget would be nice.
